### Highlights

- We're thrilled to announce the public preview launch of our latest Azure API Management pricing tiers: Basic v2 and Standard v2. ([Docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/azure/api-management/v2-service-tiers-overview))
- API Management is now Generally Available in 2 new Azure Regions: Israel Central, Italy North.


### New features, fixes and improvements

- There is now support for timeout-ms in forward-request policy (subsecond timeout).
- The use of Bearer and other authorization schemas for custom header in validate-jwt policy is now allowed.
- Developer Portal UI is now calling DataAPI endpoints instead of SMAPI management endpoints for managed only.
- We fixed an issue where the large Azure Monitor request entry blocks Azure monitor log stream.
- We fixed and issue where the emit-metric policy can fail request when no diagnostics are configured at any scope.
- We fixed an issue where the request to grapqhl api with empty graphql resolver policy fails request.
- We fixed an issue in the test console that was not switching APIs appropriately.
- We fixed an issue where the headers were not displaying the correct information when sending request from the test console.
- We fixed an issue with publisher where there was not enough memory to create a snapshot. The default application pool memory recycle limit setting has been adjusted.


### Developer portal releases

- No releases.

